    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="325"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2636</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spring Rice</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 111</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received April 27</hi>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note of the 22d instant I
                    have the honour to inform you that according to a telegram which I have received
                    from <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> the instructions of
                    October 20 for the guidance of British sea captains, which have been
                    communicated to your Government contain the orders at present in force.</p>
                <p>You will no doubt observe that the instructions contained in your note under
                    reply were issued before the above-named date.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cecil Spring Rice</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
